# Task 2 - Network Security & Scanning

## Tools Used
- Whois
- Nslookup
- Google Dorking
- Nmap
- Netcat (nc)
- Wireshark
- iptables

## Passive Reconnaissance
- Whois = finds who owns a domain, registration details, expiry date
- Nslookup = finds IP address of a domain
- Google Dorking = uses Google search operators to find exposed files

## Google Dorking Commands Used
- site:gov.in filetype:pdf = finds PDFs on government sites
- site:gov.in filetype:xls = finds Excel files on government sites
- intitle:"index of" "parent directory" site:gov.in = finds open directories

## Active Reconnaissance
- Ping Sweep = checks which devices are alive on network
- Banner Grabbing = reveals what software a server is running

## Nmap Scans
- nmap -sS = TCP SYN scan (stealth scan)
- nmap -sV = service version detection
- nmap -O = OS detection

## Wireshark Packet Analysis
- HTTP filter = captures unencrypted web traffic
- DNS filter = captures domain name lookups
- ICMP filter = captures ping packets

## Firewall Basics (iptables)
- iptables -L = list all rules
- iptables -A INPUT -p tcp --dport 80 -j DROP = block port 80
- iptables -A INPUT -s [IP] -j DROP = block specific IP
- iptables -D = delete a rule
- iptables -F = clear all rules

## Key Concepts Learned
- Passive recon = gathering info without touching target
- Active recon = directly interacting with target
- Ports = doors on a device, each runs a different service
- Firewall = security guard that blocks/allows tr
